ce:section.ce:para:
Finally, Fluorescence-based assays were used to detect the ROSs. The SOSG (Singlet Oxygen Sensor Green Reagent), HPF (hydroxyphenyl fluorescein), and DHE (dihydroethidium) were analyzed for Singlet oxygen (
1
O 2
), hydroxyl radicals (
·
O H
), and superoxide anions (
O 2
· -
). In brief, 62.5 µg/mL of a GQD, GQD@PVDF-TrFE NPs and HNPs mixture containing 10 mM SOSG was prepared, and a fraction of the mixture was analyzed for fluorescence analysis using a microplate reader at a wavelength of 475 nm. The cell cultures were irradiated for 0 or 10 min using a 500-W Xenon lamp with an intensity of 6.5 mW cm−2. For the measurement of superoxide anion and hydroxyl radical before and after illumination, 100 µL of either NPs (62.5 g/mL) containing 10 µM HPF or 100 µM DHE was prepared, and fluorescence analysis was performed on a 96-well plate with a microplate reader at a wavelength of 490 nm.
